    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">7, Brook Street, | Grosvenor Square. W.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Oct 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>/81.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Mr Darwin.</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Will you kindly permit me to recall my name to your memory by the pamphlet on the production of a particular form of septisaemia by certain salivas, a copy of which I send herewith.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
                    <p>I promised you this in the very pleasant five minutes which I spent with you at Sir James Pagets on the first day of the Medical Congress.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> Since then I have been in Russia, and on my return find that the pamphlet (which I had sent for) has arrived.</p>
                    <p>I had the pleasure of dining last night with D<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Lauder Brunton and Norman Moore and we talked much of you.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>It is due to their encouragement that I venture to ask whether I could come out to see you next Sunday Afternoon.</p>
<p>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> W. M. Ord.<ref target="#foot.f4"/> with whom I am staying— the Dean of St Thomas’s Hospital Medical School,— is also very desirous of meeting you and would I think come with me upon very small encouragement.</p>
<p>If this proposed invasion will be convenient to you will you kindly send a line to me to that effect.</p>
<p>With the greatest respect | Very Sincerely Yours | J S Billings. </p>
                    <p rend="left">Chas Darwin</p>
                </div>
            </div>
